<body>
    <h1>Prompts User Manual</h1>

    <h2>Add New Prompt</h2>
    <p>
        To add a new prompt, follow these steps:
    </p>
    <ol>
        <li>Select a category.</li>
        <li>Select a subcategory.</li>
        <li>Type in the transcript.</li>
        <li>Click "Save" to add the prompt.</li>
    </ol>
    <img src="/images/prompts-1.png" />
    <h2>Prompt List</h2>
    <p>
        The prompt list displays 100 rows with the following columns: ID, Transcript, Category, Date Added, and Actions.
    </p>

    <h3>Prompt Status Toggle</h3>
    <p>
        Use the radio buttons to toggle between prompt status "Yes" or "No." The available actions depend on the prompt status.
    </p>

    <h4>If Prompt Status is "Yes"</h4>
    <ul>
        <li>Edit: Clicking "Edit" allows you to reselect categories and edit the transcripts.</li>
        <li>Delete: Clicking "Delete" will prompt you for confirmation to remove the prompt permanently.</li>
    </ul>

    <img src="/images/prompts-2.png" />

    <h4>Upon clicking Edit</h4>
    <img src="/images/prompts-4.png" />

    <h4>If Prompt Status is "No"</h4>
    <ul>
        <li>Set Active: Clicking "Set Active" will prompt you for confirmation to set the prompt active.</li>
    </ul>
    <img src="/images/prompts-3.png" />
    <h2>Search Bar</h2>
    <p>
        Use the search bar to filter the records as you type. The list will update dynamically based on your input.
    </p>
</body>
